.el .ds Aq '
.TH nixling-shell 1 1970-01-01 nixling "nixling CLI"
.SH NAME
shell \- Attach to or manage persistent named guest shells
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshell\fR [\fB\-\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-human\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIVM\fR> [\fIACTION\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Attach to or manage persistent named guest shells
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-name\fR \fI<NAME>\fR
Persistent shell session name. Omit to use the VM\*(Aqs configured default
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Detach an existing attached client before attaching to this session
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Render machine\-readable JSON
.TP
\fB\-\-human\fR
Render human\-readable output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIVM\fR>
VM name as declared in `nixling.vms.<name>`
.TP
[\fIACTION\fR]
Shell action. Omit to attach to the configured default session
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
attach: Attach to a persistent shell
.IP \(bu 2
list: List persistent shell sessions on a VM
.IP \(bu 2
detach: Detach a persistent shell session without killing it
.IP \(bu 2
kill: Kill a persistent shell session by name
.RE
.SH EXTRA
Forms:
  nixling shell <vm> [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-force]
  nixling shell <vm> attach [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-force]
  nixling shell <vm> list [\-\-json]
  nixling shell <vm> detach [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-json]
  nixling shell <vm> kill \-\-name NAME [\-\-json]

`nixling shell` opens persistent interactive sessions. Use `nixling vm exec <vm> \-\- <cmd>` for one\-off commands.
